This application needs at least 2 arguments MON, ARG. The final argument SIM is optional and taken care of by the
simulation ui.

MON VALUE	MEANING
0		monitor off
1		monitor on

ARG VALUE	TOP DETECTION	BROADCAST		ROUTING
0		heartbeat	normal broadcast	broadcast
1		on change	normal broadcast	direct
2		on change	optimized broadcast	direct
3		on change	optimized broadcast	broadcast

SIM needs only to be specified in case of a simulation. It accepts a string in the following form:
mac0-name0-port0+mac1-name1-port1

mac0, name0 and port0 refer to the port, name and Bluetooth adress of this chat application while all other mac, name
and port values refer to neighboring chat applications.
